Sentencas: Electrolyte supported cells (ESC) with Sc2O3-stabilized ZrO2 (ScSZ) electrolytes, Gd-doped ceria (CGO) or M/CGO (M = Ni, Ru) infiltrated Sr0.94Ti0.9Nb0.1O3 (STN94) anodes and LSM/YSZ cathodes, were evaluated for their initial performance and long-term stability.
Titulo: Effect of Ru/CGO versus Ni/CGO Co-Infiltration on the Performance and Stability of STN-Based SOFCs

Sentencas: Power density for the Ru/CGO infiltrated cell reached similar to 0.7 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, 4% H2O/H-2, whereas the Ni/CGO infiltrated cell reached similar to 0.3 W cm(-2), with the current morphologies and loadings.
Titulo: Effect of Ru/CGO versus Ni/CGO Co-Infiltration on the Performance and Stability of STN-Based SOFCs

Sentencas: Operation at 0.125 A cm(-2), 850 degrees C, feeding 50% H2O/H-2 to the node and air to the cathode, for a period >300 h showed superior stability for h Ru/CGO infiltrated cell, with similar to 0.04 mV h(-1) degradation rate, when compared to the infiltrated Ni/CGO infiltrated cell (similar to 0.5 mV h(-1)).
Titulo: Effect of Ru/CGO versus Ni/CGO Co-Infiltration on the Performance and Stability of STN-Based SOFCs

Sentencas: For the Nu/CGO case, he observed degradation has been tentatively linked to initial changes in the electrochemical active area and long-term detrimental interactions between components.
Titulo: Effect of Ru/CGO versus Ni/CGO Co-Infiltration on the Performance and Stability of STN-Based SOFCs
